President Trump delivered remarks in the Rose Garden at the White House, where he discussed the strong performance of the stock market and expressed gratitude for the country's prosperity. He also welcomed guests, including Representatives David Rouzer and Jason Smith, and praised their contributions. The President acknowledged the tradition of pardoning a Thanksgiving turkey, and introduced this year's turkeys, Butter and Bread, who were raised in North Carolina. He joked about the turkeys being subpoenaed to appear in Adam Schiff's basement and issued a full pardon for Butter. President Trump concluded his remarks by wishing all Americans a happy and blessed Thanksgiving.